C. Memmius Gemellus was an enemy of Caesar. and afterwards being condemned De Ambitu he went to Athens. Three ofCicero’s letters to him are extant (Ad Fam. xiii. 1, 2, 3). Lucretius dedicated his poem to this master of Greek literature, who cared little for the literature of his own nation (Cicero, Brutus, c. 70). Memmius gave Vatinius notice of trial (ut adesset).
